Issue 215 | The New Aesthetic – Art From The Outer Limits

Alongside an illuminating, inspiring interview with 91-year-old fashion muse Iris Apfel by Karley Sciortino and photoshoot by Jeff Bark and styled by Dazed's Robbie Spencer is the scoop on Fatima Al-Qadiri's jaw-droppingly brutal imagining of Gulf futurism. Rounding up our issue on art's outer edge is a chat between Philip Glass and Beck on their collaborative remix project and Francesca Gavin's identification of the Off Modernists, plus six original artworks by this thrilling new breed.

An exclusive stream of Sushi, the new LP for Hippos In Tanks by the hi-def-lo-fi pop-art musician
The record will be out on November 7th digitally, and on CD & LP on December 10th - stream it in full exclusively here first on Dazed:
The experimental NYC -> Los Angeles-based underground electronic producer

artistically creates unhinged psychedelic digital experiences with his work. Fabricating richly textured musical journeys through chopped up Rihanna vocal samples to soaring ethereal synths and abstract FX, Ferraro with his new album
manages to transport the listener to epic futuristic dreamworlds.

Endlessly progressive, Ferraro has always been evolutionary in his music, releasing under several monikers and initially using more lo-fi guitar-heavy instrumentals. Whereas his previous album in 2011,
, was seemingly honed around the retro aesthetics of 90s PC game soundtracks to entrancing and sometimes almost comic effect. It's no surprise that for his latest venture arriving as his second LP on
, Ferraro has progressed his sounds to a more modern take in leftfield electronica.
"Sushi is designer, Sushi is my obsessions, my darkness, it's just my life squeezed into my music"
